<h1>The Paper Game — what is it?</h1>
<p>
  The Paper Game is a game of humor, creativity, and wild misinterpretation. You'll write, you'll draw, and you'll laugh!
</p>
<h2>How do I play?</h2>
<p>
  The rules are simple. First, everyone writes a sentence – any sentence! – which gets sent to the next player down the line. That player then reads the setence and draws a picture that portrays the scenario in the sentence. The picture then gets passed on to the next player, who writes a sentence describing the picture.
</p>
<p>
  <strong>In short, if you're looking at a picture, describe it; if you're reading a sentence, draw it.</strong> And that's it!
</p>
<p>
  Here are few tips to help you on your way:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Have fun!</strong> Absurd sentences are more than okay!</li>
  <li><strong>Can't draw?</strong> Don't worry, bad drawings are better! If the next player can perfectly reconstruct the original sentence from your picture, the game hasn't really moved forward, has it?</li>
  <li><strong>Or maybe don't draw at all.</strong> If you'd rather break out the Play-Doh and photograph your subject or what have you, you can upload any picture you want. Just keep in mind that it will be resized to 500-by-300 in the default view.</li>
  <li><strong>You don't have to be literal!</strong> Maybe those three trick-or-treaters are Pinky, Inky, and Blinky in a desperate search for Clyde. Some people just add sheep to everything.</li>
  <li><strong>Or maybe be too literal.</strong> If you get a sentence about a couple "making love" but you hate drawing beds, perhaps they are working on an assembly line or something? I don't know, that's your problem now; just remember the most important thing:</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <strong>HAVE FUN!</strong>
</p>
